<subSubSection id="11CBB0C0FFEBFFA6FF1B6F590BDADA73" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" type="description">
<paragraph id="596EE34BFFEBFFA6FF1B6F590B4EDF97" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FF1B6F59093BDF7F" bold="true" box="[199,345,259,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="866A5DE9FFEBFFA6FEBC6F5E09AADF7E" box="[352,456,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FE136F5E0A7DDF7F" box="[463,543,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="95.0">95 mm</quantity>
by 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FD966F5E0AEEDF7F" box="[586,652,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
at x, 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FD106F5E0B6FDF7F" box="[716,781,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
at clitellum, 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FC7F6F5E0B87DF7F" box="[931,997,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
at xxx, 284 segments; 
<typeStatus id="866A5DE9FFEBFFA6FB366F5F0D37DF7E" box="[1258,1365,261,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">paratypes</typeStatus>
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FA816F5E08A1DF5C" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.225" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="92.25">92.25 mm</quantity>
by 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FF2A6F7D0933DF5C" box="[246,337,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
at x, 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FE416F7D099ADF5C" box="[413,504,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
at clitellum and 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FD1A6F7D0B4DDF5C" box="[710,815,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="4.25">4.25 mm</quantity>
at xxx, 241 segments. Body cylindrical and slightly flattened. Setae 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FEBE6F16091CDF07" box="[354,382,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">ab</emphasis>
commence on iii. Setae closely paired throughout; setal formula 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FB176F160D1BDF07" box="[1227,1401,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">aa:ab:bc:cd:dd</emphasis>
= 0.7:0.7:0.5:0.6:2 at xxx. Prostomium tentacular, post-setal secondary annulations present viii–xiv and after clitellum (
<figureCitation id="C1EAFFCEFFEBFFA6FED66FCE092FDFCF" box="[266,333,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,406,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,371,1916]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Righiodrilus viseuensis n. sp. A. Lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. B. Ventral view of anterior body with clitellum. C. Photography of lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. D. Spermathecae of vi – viii. E. Dorsal view of calciferous gland of xii. F. Photography of dorsal view showing gizzard (segment vi), spermathecae (segments vi, vii and viii) and calciferous gland (segment xii); g = gizzard, s = spermathecae, c = calciferous gland. G. Somatic seta A of xv." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376473/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C). Unpigmented, clitellum whitish. Ovipores in 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FCAE6FCE0BE2DFCF" box="[882,896,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">b</emphasis>
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FC5B6FCE0BBFDFCF" box="[903,989,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
apart on xiv; male pores 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FB256FCE0D59DFCF" box="[1273,1339,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
apart on xix within paired oval dimpled porophores; clitellum saddle to just above 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FBC76FE20C4BDFB3" box="[1051,1065,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">b</emphasis>
, xvi–xxiii (
<figureCitation id="C1EAFFCEFFEBFFA6FB646FED0D60DFB3" box="[1208,1282,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,406,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,371,1916]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Righiodrilus viseuensis n. sp. A. Lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. B. Ventral view of anterior body with clitellum. C. Photography of lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. D. Spermathecae of vi – viii. E. Dorsal view of calciferous gland of xii. F. Photography of dorsal view showing gizzard (segment vi), spermathecae (segments vi, vii and viii) and calciferous gland (segment xii); g = gizzard, s = spermathecae, c = calciferous gland. G. Somatic seta A of xv." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376473/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A); tubercula pubertatis in xix–xxiii (
<figureCitation id="C1EAFFCEFFEBFFA6FE426F860983DF97" box="[414,481,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,406,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,371,1916]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Righiodrilus viseuensis n. sp. A. Lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. B. Ventral view of anterior body with clitellum. C. Photography of lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. D. Spermathecae of vi – viii. E. Dorsal view of calciferous gland of xii. F. Photography of dorsal view showing gizzard (segment vi), spermathecae (segments vi, vii and viii) and calciferous gland (segment xii); g = gizzard, s = spermathecae, c = calciferous gland. G. Somatic seta A of xv." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376473/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A,B). Nephropores within 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FCD76F860B47DF97" box="[779,805,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">bc</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="596EE34BFFEBFFA6FF1B6C5A0B28DC8C" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">
Septa 
<date id="2D6FC58BFFEBFFA6FED36C5A0926DC7B" box="[271,324,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" value="2012-09">9/10</date>
, 
<date id="2D6FC58BFFEBFFA6FE8E6C5A0A69DC7B" box="[338,523,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" value="2012-10-11" valueMax="2012-10-11" valueMin="2012-10-11">10/11 and 11/12</date>
thin; 6/7, 7/8 and 8/9 equally thick and muscular. Alimentary canal with large cylindrical gizzard in vi; esophagus with high lamellae in chevron pattern vii–xi, valvular in xiv, intestinal origin xv; typhlosole origin xvi, xvii–xxxiii simple lamina in zig-zag with ventral edge bent over to form pockets, simple lamina xxxiv–xliv, after xliv becoming triple lamina. Calciferous glands paired xii, under seminal vesicles, composite-tubular 
<typeStatus id="866A5DE9FFEBFFA6FEB16CCA09C2DCCB" box="[365,416,656,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">type</typeStatus>
, comma-shaped, pedunculated (
<figureCitation id="C1EAFFCEFFEBFFA6FCCD6CD50B3ADCCB" box="[785,856,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,406,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,371,1916]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Righiodrilus viseuensis n. sp. A. Lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. B. Ventral view of anterior body with clitellum. C. Photography of lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. D. Spermathecae of vi – viii. E. Dorsal view of calciferous gland of xii. F. Photography of dorsal view showing gizzard (segment vi), spermathecae (segments vi, vii and viii) and calciferous gland (segment xii); g = gizzard, s = spermathecae, c = calciferous gland. G. Somatic seta A of xv." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376473/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
E); blood vessels to gland include large branch of dorsal vessel to approximate center of each gland. Calcium carbonate reservoir shape conical. Holonephric, vesiculate; nephridial ducts to body wall near level of 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FD2A6C820B66DC93" box="[758,772,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">b</emphasis>
setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="596EE34BFFEBFFA6FF1B6CA60BDADA73" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">
Vascular system with ventral trunk, single dorsal trunk, lateral vessels in vii–ix, latero-esophageal hearts in x– xi, last pair (xi) enclosed in testis sacs. Extra-esophageal vessel from pharyngeal glands, along ventral-lateral face of gizzard, esophagus back to calciferous glands; supraesophageal vessel in x–xi. Ovaries, ovarian funnels free in xiii; three pairs of spermathecae in segments vi, vii and viii; spermathecae rounded and convex (
<figureCitation id="C1EAFFCEFFEBFFA6FB356D3D0D4CDDE3" box="[1257,1326,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,406,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,371,1916]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Righiodrilus viseuensis n. sp. A. Lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. B. Ventral view of anterior body with clitellum. C. Photography of lateral view of anterior body with clitellum. D. Spermathecae of vi – viii. E. Dorsal view of calciferous gland of xii. F. Photography of dorsal view showing gizzard (segment vi), spermathecae (segments vi, vii and viii) and calciferous gland (segment xii); g = gizzard, s = spermathecae, c = calciferous gland. G. Somatic seta A of xv." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376473/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D,F), size 1.24x 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FF086DD60950DDC7" box="[212,306,908,932]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23mm</quantity>
to 0.90x 
<quantity id="9E294EAEFFEBFFA6FE716DD60A6EDDC7" box="[429,524,908,932]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12mm</quantity>
. Male sexual system metandric, testes and funnels in single midventral subesophageal sac in xi; medial to hearts of xi pass narrow tubes to seminal vesicles; seminal vesicles expanded in xii, penetrate septa and range posteriorly along intestine to xx; seminal vesicles lobulated occupying xii to xx; vasa deferentia on body wall at 
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FE1E6DA209B2DA73" box="[450,464,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">b</emphasis>
en route to enter body wall in segment xix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11CBB0C0FFEBFFA6FF1B6A460BDCDA8B" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="596EE34BFFEBFFA6FF1B6A460BDCDA8B" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FF1B6A460959DA57" bold="true" box="[199,315,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is unique among members of the genus for having the tubercula pubertatis in xix– xxiii and clitellum in xvi–xxiii. 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FE236A1A0B66DA34" box="[511,772,1088,1112]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Righiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="viseuensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FE236A1A0B66DA34" box="[511,772,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Righiodrilus viseuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="70968222FFEBFFA6FCD06A1A0B2EDA3B" box="[780,844,1088,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" rank="species">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FCD06A1A0B2EDA3B" bold="true" box="[780,844,1088,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FC3D6A1B0CB8DA3B" authority="Righi, 1971" authorityName="Righi" authorityYear="1971" box="[993,1242,1087,1112]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Righiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tinga">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FC3D6A1B0C59DA34" box="[993,1083,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">R. tinga</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3D409EBAFFEBFFA6FB966A650CB0DA3B" author="Righi" box="[1098,1234,1087,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" refString="Righi, G. (1971) Sobre a familia Glossoscolecidae (Oligochaeta) no Brasil. Arquivos de Zoologia, 20, 1 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 20 i 1 p 1 - 95" type="journal article" year="1971">Righi, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FACE6A1B0A41DA1F" authority="Righi, Ayres &amp; Bittencourt, 1978" authorityName="Righi, Ayres &amp; Bittencourt" authorityYear="1978" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Righiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="schubarti">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FACE6A1B0DFEDA3B" box="[1298,1436,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">R. schubarti</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3D409EBAFFEBFFA6FF436A3E0A79DA1F" author="Righi" box="[159,539,1124,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" refString="Righi, G., Ayres, I. &amp; Bittencourt, E. (1978) Oligochaeta (Annelida) do Instituto Nacional de Pesquisas da Amazonia. Acta Amazonica, 8 (3), 1 (Supplement), 1 - 49." type="journal article" year="1978">Righi, Ayres &amp; Bittencourt, 1978</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the number and position of the spermathecae. 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FB8B6A3F0C80DA1F" box="[1111,1250,1124,1148]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Righiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="schubarti">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FB8B6A3F0C80DA1F" box="[1111,1250,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">R. schubarti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species by the position of the clitellum at xv–xxiv, and 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FCE76AD30BF6DAFC" box="[827,916,1160,1184]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Righiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tinga">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FCE76AD30BF6DAFC" box="[827,916,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">R. tinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species by male pores in xvii/xviii. 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FED06AF709FFDAA7" box="[268,413,1197,1220]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Righiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="viseuensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FED06AF709FFDAA7" box="[268,413,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">R. viseuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="70968222FFEBFFA6FE786AF60981DAA7" box="[420,483,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" rank="species">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FE786AF609BEDAA7" bold="true" box="[420,476,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9ED198C8FFEBFFA6FD706AF70BF6DAA7" authority="Righi, 1982" authorityName="Righi" authorityYear="1982" box="[684,916,1196,1221]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Glossodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tico">
<emphasis id="6BA53F59FFEBFFA6FD706AF70A97DAA7" box="[684,757,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">R. tico</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3D409EBAFFEBFFA6FCD86AF60BEEDAA7" author="Righi" box="[772,908,1196,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" refString="Righi, G. (1982) Oligochaeta, Glossoscolecidae, do Parque Nacional da Amazonia, Tapajos. Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 42, 107 - 116." type="journal article" year="1982">Righi, 1982</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by having the male pores in 1/2 xix; the latter species differs by the position of tubercula pubertatis in 1/2 xix–1/2 xxi.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
